olive oil
3 potato
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 Brown Onion
1 sprig spring onion
1 tomato
1 carrot
1 tin cannellini beans
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet BBQ sauce
1 packet tomato sugo
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
¼ cup water
20 g butter
1 bag baby spinach leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet sour cream
1 packet diced bacon

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place potato on a lined oven tray, then add a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt.
• Toss to coat, then arrange potato into two single layered piles. Bake for 20-25 minutes.
• When the potatoes have 5 minutes remaining, sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over each pile and bake until melted and golden, 5 minutes.

• Meanwhile, finely chop onion and spring onion. Roughly chop tomato. Grate the carrot. Drain and rinse cannellini beans.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook onion, carrot and diced bacon, breaking up bacon with a spoon, until golden, 6-7 minutes.

• Add cannellini beans, All-American spice blend and BBQ sauce to the pan and stir to combine.
• Add tomato sugo, vegetable stock powder and the water and cook, stirring, until well combined.
• Reduce heat to medium and simmer until thickened, 2-3 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then stir through the butter and baby spinach leaves, cooking until just wilted, 1 minute.

• In a medium bowl, combine tomato and spring onion. Add a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste and set aside.

• Divide cheesy baked potatoes between bowls and spoon over smokey bacon and bean chilli.
• Top with tomato salsa and dollop with sour cream to serve. Enjoy!